
I completed the required preparation, assessment, and assignment tasks. 
The focus of this week was understanding the Danish job market, 
reflecting on my career status, and beginning the process of improving my professional profile.

Preparation & Assessment Completed
Studied the difference between hard skills and soft skills and reflected on how both apply to my professional background
Read materials about working in Denmark, including employment conditions, A-kasse, unions, and contracts
Reviewed information about Danish work culture and compared it with my previous work experience
These activities helped me better understand employer expectations in Denmark and assess how my skills and experience fit into the local job market.

Assignment Work Completed
Read the HackYourFuture CV Guide and reviewed CV best practices
Updated my LinkedIn profile to better reflect my background and career direction
Added my email, LinkedIn, and GitHub links to my Slack profile
Wrote a short professional profile text and added it to my CV
Updated my CV, including work experience, technical skills, and soft skills
Improved CV structure and clarity using a clean and professional template
Considered ATS compatibility to ensure my CV is readable by recruitment systems

Key Reflections & Learnings
Gained a clearer understanding of how recruitment works in Denmark
Became more aware of my transferable skills and professional strengths
Improved my ability to present my experience in a structured and relevant way
Increased confidence in describing my career background and future goals
Identified areas for further improvement, especially in tailoring my profile for developer roles

